<p>Also, can I just summarize your argument here?<br />
1) A singularity is a coordinate in space time where the math breaks down. Where things go so non-linear we can&#8217;t predict anything.<br />
2) I know that the singularity is coming in 2045. Precisely.<br />
3) After the singularity, on the other side of that unknowable boundary, we are going to have no material needs and our political system will magically line up with the new reality of perpetual abundance.<br />
4) Thus sayeth the Lord. QED.  </p>
<p>Did I get it right? :)</p>
